WEBVTT

00:00:22.219 --> 00:00:25.559
Then he said, a certain man had two sons,

00:00:25.559 --> 00:00:28.399
and the younger of them said to his father.

00:00:28.399 --> 00:00:30.920
Father, give me the part of the property that

00:00:30.920 --> 00:00:32.399
falls to my share.

00:00:32.399 --> 00:00:35.840
Then he divided his means of living to them.

00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:39.079
Later, after not many days, the younger son

00:00:39.079 --> 00:00:42.079
gathered all things together and traveled abroad

00:00:42.079 --> 00:00:47.079
into a distant country, their squandered his property

00:00:47.079 --> 00:00:49.640
by living a debauched life.

00:00:49.640 --> 00:00:55.399
Then he said to him, child, you have always been with me

00:00:55.399 --> 00:00:58.679
and all the things that our mind are yours.

00:00:58.679 --> 00:01:02.159
But we just had to enjoy ourselves and rejoice.

00:01:02.159 --> 00:01:06.280
Because this, your brother was dead and came to life.

00:01:06.280 --> 00:01:17.530
And he was lost and was found.

00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:18.810
I see that, David.

00:01:18.810 --> 00:01:53.010
I need you to do it.

00:01:53.010 --> 00:01:54.290
We live yet.

00:01:54.290 --> 00:01:56.090
Who wants to know?

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:57.129
Come on, little brother.

00:01:57.129 --> 00:01:59.769
Get him move on.

00:01:59.769 --> 00:02:04.250
I need some help moving the extension ladder before we eat.

00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:46.250
Not today, big brother.

00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:47.370
Hey, James, hold on.

00:02:47.370 --> 00:02:48.449
That's a two-man job.

00:02:48.449 --> 00:02:53.360
OK, let me give you a hand.

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:56.639
You know it's a two-man job.

00:02:56.639 --> 00:02:58.919
You have the mansion and down here by now to help.

00:02:58.919 --> 00:03:01.879
Your brother's going for a job interview in the city.

00:03:01.879 --> 00:03:03.719
Job interview for what?

00:03:03.719 --> 00:03:05.520
Where did this come from?

00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:10.840
You told me and your mother about it last night.

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:14.599
That'll work out really well with the schedule.

00:03:14.599 --> 00:03:16.479
Uh-huh.

00:03:16.479 --> 00:03:22.710
OK, yes.

00:03:22.710 --> 00:03:26.189
And 50% at the end of the month.

00:03:26.189 --> 00:03:31.580
That's right.

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:35.810
And I'll make sure John gets back to you on that.

00:03:35.810 --> 00:03:37.490
You're welcome.

00:03:37.490 --> 00:03:38.849
Bye-bye.

00:03:38.849 --> 00:03:40.129
Mom, I got to go.

00:03:40.129 --> 00:03:41.610
Honey, you're not staying for breakfast?

00:03:41.610 --> 00:03:42.569
No, I can't.

00:03:42.569 --> 00:03:45.210
Here, John, the Crawfords accepted your bid.

00:03:45.210 --> 00:03:45.729
OK.

00:03:45.729 --> 00:03:47.610
Hey, Dad, hey, David, you're not eating with us.

00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:48.810
No, I got to go.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:51.210
But breakfast is almost ready.

00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:53.729
David, I'd sure like to talk with you before you go.

00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:55.370
Yeah, why don't you join us for a while?

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:57.930
We can talk about things like, you know, the weather.

00:03:57.930 --> 00:03:59.889
And how you never told your older brother

00:03:59.889 --> 00:04:01.729
that you were looking for another job.

00:04:01.729 --> 00:04:02.810
I'm sorry.

00:04:02.810 --> 00:04:04.889
I didn't know I needed your permission.

00:04:04.889 --> 00:04:06.770
Have you forgotten that you have a job?

00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:08.569
Barker, family, construction?

00:04:08.569 --> 00:04:11.050
You know, the small company that you're 25% of?

00:04:11.050 --> 00:04:13.169
The one that finally has workbook for six months?

00:04:13.169 --> 00:04:15.250
John, can you stir that for me, please?

00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:17.209
OK, first, it's just an interview.

00:04:17.209 --> 00:04:18.610
I haven't actually gotten a job.

00:04:18.610 --> 00:04:20.610
And second, maybe I don't want to swing a hammer

00:04:20.610 --> 00:04:22.370
for the rest of my life.

00:04:22.410 --> 00:04:24.250
And what's wrong with that?

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:25.529
Nothing.

00:04:25.529 --> 00:04:29.250
I just want to get out of my own, maybe have more responsibility.

00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:31.009
David, I told you, you're almost at a point

00:04:31.009 --> 00:04:32.810
when I can give you some jobs of your own.

00:04:32.810 --> 00:04:37.009
You do good work, and you're only getting better.

00:04:37.009 --> 00:04:39.370
So what is this dream job that you're after anyway?

00:04:39.370 --> 00:04:41.449
It's a web marketing company in the city.

00:04:41.449 --> 00:04:42.769
Web marketing?

00:04:42.769 --> 00:04:44.649
What experience are you have with that?

00:04:44.649 --> 00:04:45.209
None.

00:04:45.209 --> 00:04:48.370
But they're hiring for some big project in Al recommended me.

00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:50.850
I'm meeting him first to get some tips before the interview.

00:04:50.850 --> 00:04:53.810
Tips from L. I mean, L Phillips.

00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:55.610
Please don't tell me you've revived your friendship

00:04:55.610 --> 00:04:56.490
with L loser.

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.370
He's not a loser.

00:04:58.370 --> 00:05:00.129
He's been with the company for two years,

00:05:00.129 --> 00:05:01.649
and he's already a project manager.

00:05:01.649 --> 00:05:03.129
I'm sorry, I'll rephrase that.

00:05:03.129 --> 00:05:04.370
He's a spiritual loser.

00:05:04.370 --> 00:05:07.129
You know, James, it's amazing to me that you have time

00:05:07.129 --> 00:05:09.370
to be both a carpenter and a judge.

00:05:09.370 --> 00:05:13.050
OK, OK, it's time to eat, honey.

00:05:13.050 --> 00:05:17.050
Let's do our daily texts and then feed these monkeys.

00:05:17.050 --> 00:05:18.490
I think that's a good idea.

00:05:18.490 --> 00:05:20.689
Mom, Dad, I'm sorry.

00:05:20.689 --> 00:05:22.610
But I'm going to have to do it later.

00:05:22.610 --> 00:05:25.810
I'm a little nervous, and I want to get there early.

00:05:25.810 --> 00:05:27.689
All right, then, you better get going.

00:05:27.689 --> 00:05:29.850
But please, before you agree to anything,

00:05:29.850 --> 00:05:31.370
let's talk about it first, OK?

00:05:31.370 --> 00:05:32.449
Absolutely, Dad.

00:05:32.449 --> 00:05:33.889
It's just an interview.

00:05:33.889 --> 00:05:34.810
All right.

00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:36.810
Well, you need something to eat.

00:05:36.810 --> 00:05:39.810
And remember, tonight, I'm making your favorite roast beef.

00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:40.689
Sounds great.

00:05:40.689 --> 00:05:42.129
Thanks, Mom.

00:05:42.129 --> 00:05:42.810
Love you.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:43.889
Love you too, honey.

00:05:43.889 --> 00:05:45.410
Love you, son.

00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:47.009
They remember you have a talk tonight.

00:05:47.009 --> 00:05:50.720
Yep, I'm all set.

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:53.079
So what if he actually gets this job?

00:05:53.079 --> 00:05:54.160
Are you really going to let him just

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.600
quit in the middle of all this work?

00:05:56.600 --> 00:05:58.120
Well, I guess there's no sense in worrying about what

00:05:58.120 --> 00:05:59.759
hasn't happened yet.

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:02.079
Besides, it's not like I can force him or you

00:06:02.079 --> 00:06:04.000
for that matter to work for me.

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:07.199
Dad, I want to work with you.

00:06:07.199 --> 00:06:09.519
I appreciate that, son.

00:06:09.519 --> 00:06:11.879
Well, let's do our daily texts.

00:06:11.879 --> 00:06:13.000
No, don't get me wrong.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.120
I'm definitely so excited about this opportunity.

00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:17.120
It's just my family, isn't it?

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:19.439
Brother is such a control freak, man.

00:06:19.439 --> 00:06:20.639
He's just a mellow out.

00:06:20.639 --> 00:06:22.360
He's going to have a stroke or something.

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:23.279
Oh, yeah, right.

00:06:23.279 --> 00:06:24.920
My main concern is my parents.

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:26.800
I don't think they want me to leave the family business.

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:29.560
And my dad wonders if this is the best move for me.

00:06:29.560 --> 00:06:32.480
Classic case of parents not wanting to let go.

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:35.199
But look, years from now, when their old and feeble

00:06:35.199 --> 00:06:37.959
and barker family construction is going to under,

00:06:37.959 --> 00:06:40.560
they are going to be so grateful that their son

00:06:40.560 --> 00:06:43.519
is a rock solid job with a Fortune 500 company.

00:06:43.519 --> 00:06:44.240
He might as well.

00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:45.480
I'm right.

00:06:45.480 --> 00:06:46.519
Here we are.

00:06:46.519 --> 00:06:47.720
Wow.

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.040
Is it the whole building?

00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:51.319
No, it's just two floors.

00:06:51.319 --> 00:06:52.319
You think I stand a chance?

00:06:52.319 --> 00:06:59.540
Of course.

00:06:59.540 --> 00:07:00.899
He's with me.

00:07:00.899 --> 00:07:02.779
They don't let you stay here.

00:07:02.779 --> 00:07:04.459
All right, let's go over this one more time.

00:07:04.459 --> 00:07:06.019
You got to sell them on your strengths.

00:07:06.019 --> 00:07:07.220
You're a good worker.

00:07:07.220 --> 00:07:08.660
Excellent communicator.

00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:09.420
Quick learner.

00:07:09.420 --> 00:07:10.500
Can do, can a guy.

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:11.500
Got it.

00:07:11.500 --> 00:07:13.180
You got to sell like a company, man.

00:07:13.180 --> 00:07:13.980
Yes, sir.

00:07:13.980 --> 00:07:15.939
Do whatever it takes or whatever you need.

00:07:15.939 --> 00:07:16.699
Stuff like that.

00:07:16.699 --> 00:07:17.540
It's very important.

00:07:17.540 --> 00:07:27.439
Right, right.

00:07:27.439 --> 00:07:29.560
So let me be frank.

00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.399
You don't have any experience in web marketing

00:07:32.439 --> 00:07:34.399
or with any marketing for that matter.

00:07:34.399 --> 00:07:41.180
Yes, sir, but I learned very quickly.

00:07:41.180 --> 00:07:43.300
This is tough.

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:44.379
I like you.

00:07:44.379 --> 00:07:45.819
I like your attitude.

00:07:45.819 --> 00:07:47.740
And I'm impressed with the way you speak.

00:07:47.740 --> 00:07:48.540
Thank you, sir.

00:07:48.540 --> 00:07:50.939
I appreciate that.

00:07:50.939 --> 00:07:52.779
Tell me in your construction job,

00:07:52.779 --> 00:07:55.379
how many hours a day did you work?

00:07:55.379 --> 00:08:01.519
Mostly eight, sometimes less.

00:08:01.519 --> 00:08:06.310
How would you do working a professional week?

00:08:06.310 --> 00:08:07.029
Fine.

00:08:07.029 --> 00:08:08.670
How would be no problem?

00:08:08.670 --> 00:08:50.360
I'll do whatever it takes, whatever you need.

00:08:50.360 --> 00:09:07.879
David, David, won't you come on back?

00:09:07.879 --> 00:09:09.600
Got something to tell you.

00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:10.960
Let me guess.

00:09:10.960 --> 00:09:12.960
I don't have enough experience.

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:13.879
That's right.

00:09:13.879 --> 00:09:15.759
You don't.

00:09:15.759 --> 00:09:17.919
But it doesn't matter.

00:09:17.919 --> 00:09:19.159
He really likes you.

00:09:19.159 --> 00:09:20.200
He's going to offer you the job.

00:09:20.200 --> 00:09:20.720
No way.

00:09:20.720 --> 00:09:21.240
Really?

00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:23.320
Oh, and it gets better since you're such a rookie.

00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:25.519
He wants you on my team so I get to train you.

00:09:25.519 --> 00:09:26.440
Seriously?

00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:30.519
Yeah, so you don't feel free to refer to me as, sir, from now on.

00:09:30.519 --> 00:09:31.440
Let's go, he's waiting.

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:33.399
Right.

00:09:33.399 --> 00:09:34.360
Actually, wait.

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:36.200
What's wrong?

00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:39.360
You think I can tell Mike that I'll give him an answer tomorrow?

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:40.879
That would be a very bad idea.

00:09:40.879 --> 00:09:42.840
I know, but my dad wanted me to talk with him

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:43.919
before I committed to anything.

00:09:43.919 --> 00:09:44.919
What's there to talk about?

00:09:44.919 --> 00:09:47.519
You have 100 other people out there that want this job.

00:09:47.519 --> 00:09:48.639
I know, I want this.

00:09:48.639 --> 00:09:51.279
Then stop letting them mess with your head.

00:09:51.279 --> 00:09:54.759
This guilt, it's not healthy, bro.

00:09:54.759 --> 00:09:57.360
You're just going to do it yourself to a life of working

00:09:57.360 --> 00:10:01.379
on other people's gutters and roofs.

00:10:01.379 --> 00:10:02.220
You're probably right.

00:10:02.220 --> 00:10:03.100
I know I'm right.

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:04.299
It's a gift of mine.

00:10:04.299 --> 00:10:09.600
What are you super-getting at before he changes his mind?

00:10:09.600 --> 00:10:10.879
All right, let's do it.

00:10:10.879 --> 00:10:14.440
Now you're talking.

00:10:14.440 --> 00:10:16.039
So what I can offer you as a position

00:10:16.039 --> 00:10:18.240
as a project assistant.

00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:20.519
Once you sign the company confidentiality agreement,

00:10:20.519 --> 00:10:22.120
you'll get more details.

00:10:22.120 --> 00:10:26.000
For now, this will tell you about our company.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.559
Thank you for the opportunity, Mr. Benson.

00:10:28.559 --> 00:10:31.000
