00:29:33.160 --> 00:29:34.279
Nice guy second.

00:29:34.279 --> 00:29:39.720
You see?

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:40.880
Everything OK?

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:42.039
Yeah, it's fine.

00:29:42.039 --> 00:29:44.759
Just a persistent ex-boyfriend, sorry.

00:29:44.759 --> 00:29:45.480
Let me guess.

00:29:45.480 --> 00:29:47.440
The guy you were talking about when we first met?

00:29:47.440 --> 00:29:49.160
I have a good memory.

00:29:49.160 --> 00:29:52.000
Yes, another tragic love story.

00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:55.000
Girl gives her heart to guy, and guy cheats on her.

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:58.480
They break up, and guy tries to win her back.

00:29:58.480 --> 00:30:00.160
Taylor, I haven't known you that long,

00:30:00.160 --> 00:30:04.000
but I'm pretty sure you deserve a whole lot better than that.

00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:05.200
Thank you.

00:30:05.200 --> 00:30:07.400
I think so too.

00:30:07.400 --> 00:30:08.799
Well, now that you know all about me,

00:30:08.799 --> 00:30:10.680
I don't know very much about you.

00:30:10.680 --> 00:30:12.279
Other than you grew up with Al,

00:30:12.279 --> 00:30:13.880
you worked as a carpenter.

00:30:13.880 --> 00:30:16.480
You're a super nice guy, and you don't curse.

00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:18.240
Tell me more.

00:30:18.240 --> 00:30:19.240
That's about it.

00:30:19.240 --> 00:30:21.440
You've pretty much covered everything.

00:30:21.440 --> 00:30:23.480
Come on.

00:30:23.480 --> 00:30:25.960
Really, there's not much else.

00:30:25.960 --> 00:30:29.759
I started working for my dad's company when I was 16.

00:30:29.759 --> 00:30:31.880
Barker family construction.

00:30:31.880 --> 00:30:34.000
A forward-moving, privately-owned firm

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:37.519
based out of a modest facility, our garage,

00:30:37.519 --> 00:30:40.640
that features a highly sympathica workforce.

00:30:40.640 --> 00:30:43.480
My dad, mom, and older brother.

00:30:43.480 --> 00:30:45.440
Our mission statement?

00:30:45.440 --> 00:30:48.599
No job, too small.

00:30:48.599 --> 00:30:50.559
Sounds like a nice, cute work for it.

00:30:50.559 --> 00:30:52.880
Yeah, I guess it was.

00:30:52.880 --> 00:30:54.559
I just kind of grew out of it, you know?

00:30:54.559 --> 00:30:56.960
And it's my recent job change.

00:30:56.960 --> 00:30:58.400
Now with your construction background,

00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:01.960
how do you explain the nice guy no cursing part?

00:31:01.960 --> 00:31:03.599
That.

00:31:03.599 --> 00:31:05.880
Well, my family is very religious,

00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:08.279
so we were raised studying the Bible.

00:31:08.279 --> 00:31:10.799
OK, what religion?

00:31:10.799 --> 00:31:12.079
Christian.

00:31:12.079 --> 00:31:16.779
Well, I figured that, but what church?

00:31:16.779 --> 00:31:18.380
Where Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:31:18.380 --> 00:31:19.859
Oh, really?

00:31:19.859 --> 00:31:21.420
You know, there was a girl in high school

00:31:21.420 --> 00:31:23.579
that was Jehovah Witness.

00:31:23.579 --> 00:31:25.180
She was really, really into it.

00:31:25.180 --> 00:31:27.900
Actually, some of the kids kind of made fun of her.

00:31:27.900 --> 00:31:33.019
I tell you the truth, I don't know much about it.

00:31:33.019 --> 00:31:35.180
It looks like Al is going to send out a search party

00:31:35.180 --> 00:31:37.019
if we don't get back.

00:31:37.019 --> 00:31:38.259
I wouldn't want that now, would we?

00:31:38.259 --> 00:31:54.450
No.

00:31:54.450 --> 00:31:57.650
Research for our project?

00:31:57.650 --> 00:31:59.250
How is your coffee break?

00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:00.529
Ah, good.

00:32:00.529 --> 00:32:02.170
Why do you ask?

00:32:02.170 --> 00:32:04.609
So you are interested in it?

00:32:04.609 --> 00:32:06.529
We had coffee, that's all.

00:32:06.529 --> 00:32:08.809
Oh, sure, it starts with coffee.

00:32:08.809 --> 00:32:11.329
Now, if you don't mind, I have work to do.

00:32:11.329 --> 00:32:14.890
Actually, Romeo, I have some life-altering news for you.

00:32:14.890 --> 00:32:23.369
How about we head to the Think Tank?

00:32:23.369 --> 00:32:27.250
So, what is this life-altering news that you have for me?

00:32:27.250 --> 00:32:29.769
You remember my cousin Anta, right?

00:32:29.769 --> 00:32:31.369
Yeah, the one that lives downtown.

00:32:31.369 --> 00:32:33.849
Yeah, well, he's got to tell me that two of his roommates

00:32:33.849 --> 00:32:36.009
just moved out of the apartment.

00:32:36.009 --> 00:32:39.130
So, he's got to rent the rooms at an order

00:32:39.130 --> 00:32:40.490
for to stay there.

00:32:40.490 --> 00:32:41.450
Go on.

00:32:41.450 --> 00:32:42.650
Stuff to spell this out for you.

00:32:42.650 --> 00:32:45.329
Two rooms, two people, two miles from work.

00:32:45.329 --> 00:32:46.529
It's too good to pass up.

00:32:46.529 --> 00:32:48.250
God, it's too expensive.

00:32:48.250 --> 00:32:49.490
This is a no-brainer.

00:32:49.490 --> 00:32:52.210
You really think that we should sublet for a man-time.

00:32:52.210 --> 00:32:53.890
Think about it, no more long commute,

00:32:53.890 --> 00:32:55.569
no more getting stuck in traffic,

00:32:55.569 --> 00:32:57.369
no more having your loving family,

00:32:57.369 --> 00:32:59.490
scrutinize every movie you make.

00:32:59.490 --> 00:33:01.809
Yeah, the cherry on top is that we get to room together.

00:33:01.809 --> 00:33:05.529
Maybe forgetting that I make way less money than you.

00:33:05.529 --> 00:33:07.369
Dave, it's only a matter of time for you to get a raise.

00:33:07.369 --> 00:33:08.569
Probably a promotion.

00:33:08.569 --> 00:33:11.329
Well, until then, I can't afford it.

00:33:11.329 --> 00:33:16.589
Don't you have any savings you can tap into?

00:33:16.589 --> 00:33:19.190
Yeah, some.

00:33:19.190 --> 00:33:20.670
All right, let me talk to my parents first,

00:33:20.670 --> 00:33:24.200
and I'll get back to you.

00:33:24.200 --> 00:33:32.509
Listen, here, take a seat.

00:33:32.509 --> 00:33:33.950
I'll be up front with you.

00:33:33.950 --> 00:33:36.549
As a favor to me, Anta was willing to let you rent out

00:33:36.549 --> 00:33:39.549
the room instead of his girlfriend's brother.

00:33:39.549 --> 00:33:40.710
But you got to act now,

00:33:40.710 --> 00:33:47.240
or the deal's going to be gone by this weekend.

00:33:47.240 --> 00:33:50.160
Blake, you're 21 years old.

00:33:50.160 --> 00:33:55.279
You can't live with your parents forever.

00:33:55.279 --> 00:33:58.279
Don't you think it's time you leave the nest?

00:33:58.279 --> 00:34:00.960
Spread your wings?

00:34:00.960 --> 00:34:10.699
Be your own man.

00:34:10.699 --> 00:34:11.219
You're right.

00:34:11.219 --> 00:34:12.260
All right, I'll take it.

00:34:12.260 --> 00:34:12.780
I'm in.

00:34:12.780 --> 00:34:13.619
Fantastic.

00:34:13.619 --> 00:34:21.440
Let me just call Anta.

00:34:21.440 --> 00:34:22.440
Hey, Anta.

00:34:22.440 --> 00:34:25.480
Yeah, yeah, my boy, David's in.

00:34:25.480 --> 00:34:27.039
Tonight?

00:34:27.039 --> 00:34:28.360
Sure, Pete's.

00:34:28.360 --> 00:34:30.480
Yeah.

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:31.639
All right.

00:34:31.639 --> 00:34:32.519
OK, we'll see you there.

00:34:32.519 --> 00:34:33.320
Bye.

00:34:33.320 --> 00:34:34.000
It's done.

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:34.719
We'll meet him tonight.

00:34:34.719 --> 00:34:36.119
We'll see you the deal over a couple of years.

00:34:36.119 --> 00:34:36.800
No, we won't.

00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:37.960
I have a talk tonight.

00:34:37.960 --> 00:34:39.960
In fact, I have to finish writing it.

00:34:39.960 --> 00:34:41.280
Can't you get somebody to replace you?

00:34:41.280 --> 00:34:43.159
I hate to do that again.

00:34:43.159 --> 00:34:44.280
Just do what I do.

00:34:44.280 --> 00:34:45.199
Don't show up.

00:34:45.199 --> 00:34:46.000
Somebody always covers you.

00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:48.480
I'm not doing that.

00:34:48.480 --> 00:34:59.699
Come on, man, it's just this once.

00:34:59.699 --> 00:35:02.420
Hey, brother Harper, it's David.

00:35:02.420 --> 00:35:03.219
I'm Kid, thanks.

00:35:03.219 --> 00:35:05.059
How are you?

00:35:05.059 --> 00:35:05.980
Kid.

00:35:05.980 --> 00:35:08.219
Hey, something came up at work,

00:35:08.219 --> 00:35:10.539
and I'm not going to be able to give my talk tonight.

00:35:10.539 --> 00:35:11.340
I'm so sorry.

00:35:11.340 --> 00:35:14.820
I really hope you can find someone to cover for me.

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:17.880
I know.

00:35:17.880 --> 00:35:18.199
I know.

00:35:18.199 --> 00:35:20.199
I'm sorry.

00:35:20.199 --> 00:35:21.800
OK, thank you.

00:35:21.800 --> 00:36:01.530
All right, bye.

00:36:01.530 --> 00:36:03.650
Hello, son.

00:36:03.650 --> 00:36:06.159
Yeah.

00:36:06.159 --> 00:36:07.119
He scared me.

00:36:07.119 --> 00:36:12.110
What are you still doing up?

00:36:12.110 --> 00:36:14.710
I didn't know you had to work so late.

00:36:14.710 --> 00:36:18.030
Last night, I heard you were giving a talk tonight.

00:36:18.030 --> 00:36:19.829
I'm sorry.

00:36:19.829 --> 00:36:20.949
I should have told you.

00:36:20.949 --> 00:36:23.909
Some work-related stuff came up,

00:36:23.909 --> 00:36:27.639
and one thing led to another.

00:36:27.639 --> 00:36:31.639
Son, we need to talk.

00:36:31.639 --> 00:36:43.920
Please, would you sit down for a minute?

00:36:43.920 --> 00:36:47.760
You know, your mother and I are very worried about you.

00:36:47.760 --> 00:36:50.800
You've been missing your meetings, your service,

00:36:50.800 --> 00:36:53.760
your family worship with us.

00:36:53.760 --> 00:36:55.840
It has been happening more and more.

00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:56.960
I know, dad.

00:36:56.960 --> 00:36:59.920
It'll be a little insane just till we meet this deadline.

00:36:59.920 --> 00:37:01.960
And then what?

00:37:01.960 --> 00:37:04.760
What about the deadline after that?

00:37:04.760 --> 00:37:07.199
I used to work for a big company.

00:37:07.199 --> 00:37:11.000
The more you keep giving, the more they'll keep taking.

00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:13.480
Where are you going to draw the line?

00:37:13.480 --> 00:37:16.960
What I worked for you, we had deadlines, things that went wrong.

00:37:16.960 --> 00:37:18.039
We worked over time.

00:37:18.039 --> 00:37:19.639
Sometimes?

00:37:19.639 --> 00:37:23.320
But very rarely did it interfere with our theocratic schedule.

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:27.840
I've been pretty successful at keeping the business in its place.

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:28.840
You have, dad.

00:37:28.840 --> 00:37:29.760
I know.

00:37:29.760 --> 00:37:33.019
You said a good example that way.

00:37:33.019 --> 00:37:37.019
Why don't you consider coming back to the family business with us?

00:37:37.019 --> 00:37:42.380
You can get stabilized, and I can give you a small raise.

00:37:42.380 --> 00:37:43.260
I can't.

00:37:43.260 --> 00:37:44.300
No.

00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:46.460
Dad, I'm sorry.

00:37:46.460 --> 00:37:51.219
Construction, it's great for you and James, but not for me.

00:37:51.219 --> 00:37:54.139
I'm really happy where I met.

00:37:54.139 --> 00:38:02.469
And the people they respect me, I like this job.

00:38:02.469 --> 00:38:05.590
Is a job worth sacrificing your relationship with Jehovah?

00:38:05.590 --> 00:38:07.150
Of course not.

00:38:07.150 --> 00:38:09.230
It's not like that's happening.

00:38:09.230 --> 00:38:12.349
The Bibles filled with examples of people who felt the same way

00:38:12.349 --> 00:38:18.949
in the beginning, but then something happened gradually.

00:38:18.949 --> 00:38:24.159
I'm not quite sure how that applies to me.

00:38:24.159 --> 00:38:27.159
Here, let me show you something, David.

00:38:27.159 --> 00:38:29.039
Maybe this will help.

00:38:29.039 --> 00:38:37.480
Read Hebrews 2.1.

00:38:37.480 --> 00:38:40.320
That is why it is necessary for us to pay more

00:38:40.320 --> 00:38:43.559
than the usual attention to the things heard by us

00:38:43.559 --> 00:38:46.639
that we may never drift away.

00:38:46.639 --> 00:38:48.320
OK?

00:38:48.320 --> 00:38:52.239
We need to pay attention because any one of us could drift,

00:38:52.239 --> 00:38:56.469
and it could lead to our spiritual shipwreck.

00:38:56.469 --> 00:39:02.190
Sometimes it takes other people to point out that we're drifting.

00:39:02.190 --> 00:39:04.230
Well, I've got lots of people pointing.

00:39:04.230 --> 00:39:15.849
You, mom, James, the elders, the list is pretty long.

00:39:15.849 --> 00:39:18.210
Listen, Dad.

00:39:18.210 --> 00:39:25.829
I appreciate your concern.

00:39:25.829 --> 00:39:27.710
I need to tell you something.

00:39:27.710 --> 00:39:31.139
What is it?

00:39:31.139 --> 00:39:34.949
I'm going to move out.

00:39:34.949 --> 00:39:38.159
What?

00:39:38.159 --> 00:39:39.280
To where?

00:39:39.280 --> 00:39:40.480
Alice Cousin Anton.

00:39:40.480 --> 00:39:42.599
He's got an apartment in the city.

00:39:42.599 --> 00:39:44.840
What's wrong with living here?

00:39:44.840 --> 00:39:46.280
I need more freedom.

00:39:46.280 --> 00:39:47.800
Some independence?

00:39:47.800 --> 00:39:50.079
Freedom and independence from what?

00:39:50.079 --> 00:39:51.159
Come on, Dad.

00:39:51.159 --> 00:39:53.039
Where do I start?

00:39:53.039 --> 00:39:56.039
I feel like I'm constantly being questioned.

00:39:56.039 --> 00:39:57.440
Where are you going?

00:39:57.480 --> 00:39:59.239
Who are you with?

00:39:59.239 --> 00:40:01.360
What's the name of the movie you're seeing?

00:40:01.360 --> 00:40:04.119
Oh, he's not good association.

00:40:04.119 --> 00:40:08.400
You need to use the internet in the living room.

00:40:08.400 --> 00:40:11.599
Even when you don't see anything I can tell.

00:40:11.599 --> 00:40:14.039
I feel so restricted.

00:40:14.039 --> 00:40:16.960
David, we live by Bible principles in our house.

00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:18.199
They're not restrictive.

00:40:18.199 --> 00:40:19.679
They protect us.

00:40:19.679 --> 00:40:23.360
My point is I need to answer for myself.

00:40:23.360 --> 00:40:25.800
All of us have an accounting to God, right?

00:40:25.800 --> 00:40:26.559
That's true.

00:40:26.559 --> 00:40:30.280
I just want to make my own decisions then, right or wrong.

00:40:30.280 --> 00:40:31.760
Is that such a bad thing?

00:40:31.760 --> 00:40:34.280
If you know what's right and you choose to do what's wrong,

00:40:34.280 --> 00:40:36.119
then it is a bad thing.

00:40:36.119 --> 00:40:40.289
Honey, what's going on?

00:40:40.289 --> 00:40:42.849
What's wrong?

00:40:42.849 --> 00:40:46.500
David and I are just talking.

00:40:46.500 --> 00:40:49.659
He wants to move into the city and to an apartment

00:40:49.659 --> 00:40:52.860
with Al and his cousin Anton.

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:55.179
What?

00:40:55.179 --> 00:40:57.940
Why would you want to do that?

00:40:57.940 --> 00:41:01.380
I don't want to get into all the details right now.

00:41:01.380 --> 00:41:03.860
Let's just say it'll be a lot closer to work

00:41:03.860 --> 00:41:05.780
and we'll leave it at that.

00:41:05.780 --> 00:41:07.900
I don't understand.

00:41:07.900 --> 00:41:10.420
You have everything you need here.

00:41:10.420 --> 00:41:12.820
You save money and you're surrounded

00:41:12.820 --> 00:41:14.300
by people that love you.

00:41:14.300 --> 00:41:15.619
That's the problem.

00:41:15.619 --> 00:41:17.340
I'm feeling love to death.

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:19.420
There's no such thing.

00:41:19.420 --> 00:41:21.179
Oh, there is.

00:41:21.179 --> 00:41:24.780
And this family is a prime example.

00:41:24.780 --> 00:41:27.780
Well, what congregation would you go to?

00:41:27.780 --> 00:41:30.099
I don't know yet, Mom.

00:41:30.099 --> 00:41:32.420
Your dad knows brothers in the city.

00:41:32.420 --> 00:41:34.460
He could call someone and find out.

00:41:34.460 --> 00:41:37.340
No, that's all right.

00:41:37.340 --> 00:41:40.260
I'll take care of it when I'm ready.

00:41:40.260 --> 00:41:44.699
When you're ready, David, that's one of the first things

00:41:44.699 --> 00:41:45.780
you should find out.

00:41:45.780 --> 00:41:48.179
Mom, please.

00:41:48.179 --> 00:41:53.369
Can you even afford a place in the city?

00:41:53.369 --> 00:41:59.909
Since you asked, I'm going to need to tap into the savings

00:41:59.909 --> 00:42:02.349
account you set up for me.

00:42:02.349 --> 00:42:03.869
I was supposed to help you pioneer.

00:42:03.869 --> 00:42:05.829
It's my money, isn't it?

00:42:05.829 --> 00:42:08.110
Are you going to question how I use that also?

00:42:08.110 --> 00:42:09.030
David!

00:42:09.030 --> 00:42:13.530
No, that's all right.

00:42:13.530 --> 00:42:15.369
It's your money.

00:42:15.369 --> 00:42:17.329
Thank you.

00:42:17.329 --> 00:42:18.929
Well, well, well.

00:42:18.929 --> 00:42:21.650
What new pain are you causing the family now, little brother?

00:42:21.650 --> 00:42:23.250
Stay out of this, James.

00:42:23.250 --> 00:42:24.690
Oh, I know that's OK.

00:42:24.690 --> 00:42:26.250
I already heard most of it.

00:42:26.250 --> 00:42:30.130
So you want to move in with Elle's cousin, Anton.

00:42:30.130 --> 00:42:31.369
I wonder which one of his girlfriends is

00:42:31.369 --> 00:42:33.170
spending the night these days?

00:42:33.170 --> 00:42:35.929
You mean Anton is not in the truth?

00:42:35.929 --> 00:42:37.409
Is that true?

00:42:37.409 --> 00:42:38.690
You didn't mention that.

00:42:38.690 --> 00:42:41.369
Oh, I'm sure there's a lot more is not telling you.

00:42:41.369 --> 00:42:43.489
Now you and your mentor can really find out

00:42:43.489 --> 00:42:45.289
what this world has to offer.

00:42:45.289 --> 00:42:47.889
David, why are you putting yourself in that situation?

00:42:47.889 --> 00:42:49.010
You're just asking for trouble.

00:42:49.010 --> 00:42:50.050
It's no big deal.

00:42:50.050 --> 00:42:51.050
I can handle it.

00:42:51.050 --> 00:42:53.210
No late night at the office, huh?

00:42:53.210 --> 00:42:55.929
You know, it's so ironic that the talking

00:42:55.929 --> 00:42:59.250
card for today dealt with putting spiritual things first.

00:42:59.250 --> 00:43:00.730
Stand on my face, James.

00:43:00.730 --> 00:43:02.690
Maybe not so much ironic.

00:43:02.690 --> 00:43:06.809
Perhaps a bit more providential.

00:43:06.809 --> 00:43:10.010
I'm sure Jehovah knew you were fit to give that to us.

00:43:10.010 --> 00:43:11.690
Stop it, both of you.

00:43:11.690 --> 00:43:13.010
David, what's gotten into you?

00:43:13.010 --> 00:43:14.929
Do you see what I mean?

00:43:14.929 --> 00:43:18.969
This is exactly what I am talking about.

00:43:18.969 --> 00:43:23.570
I am done being cross-examined and scrutinized.

