01:27:31.550 --> 01:27:32.710
Morning, Mom.

01:27:32.710 --> 01:27:35.869
Well, you certainly are upright and early

01:27:35.869 --> 01:27:37.550
and making breakfast.

01:27:37.550 --> 01:27:39.829
Well, I just wanted to show the greatest moment

01:27:39.829 --> 01:27:41.350
down the world how much I love them.

01:27:41.350 --> 01:27:42.829
Oh, thank you.

01:27:42.829 --> 01:27:43.829
Of course.

01:27:43.829 --> 01:27:45.350
Well, what can I do to help?

01:27:45.350 --> 01:27:45.869
Nothing.

01:27:45.869 --> 01:27:48.069
You and Dad should just finish getting ready for meeting.

01:27:48.069 --> 01:27:49.029
Are you sure?

01:27:49.029 --> 01:27:50.069
Positive.

01:27:50.069 --> 01:27:50.909
OK.

01:27:50.909 --> 01:28:09.800
Well, I could get very used to this.

01:28:09.800 --> 01:28:16.000
James, you're home.

01:28:16.000 --> 01:28:18.979
Not for long.

01:28:18.979 --> 01:28:23.140
I just had to grab a few things.

01:28:23.140 --> 01:28:28.319
I need to say something.

01:28:28.319 --> 01:28:31.380
I'm sorry.

01:28:31.380 --> 01:28:34.680
You're sorry.

01:28:34.680 --> 01:28:36.520
Yeah.

01:28:36.520 --> 01:28:41.149
I'm sorry.

01:28:41.149 --> 01:28:43.149
Let me cut it with everyone else.

01:28:43.149 --> 01:28:45.310
But not with me.

01:28:45.310 --> 01:28:47.229
I'm not so gullible.

01:28:47.229 --> 01:28:51.510
James, please don't do this to me.

01:28:51.510 --> 01:28:56.359
To you, well, then don't do this to Mom and Dad.

01:28:56.359 --> 01:29:00.390
We can't keep putting them through this.

01:29:00.390 --> 01:29:01.670
Well, you should have thought that months ago.

01:29:01.670 --> 01:29:03.869
I know.

01:29:03.869 --> 01:29:06.869
I know this is on my fault.

01:29:06.869 --> 01:29:11.680
I wish I could go back and do things differently.

01:29:11.680 --> 01:29:14.680
Well, the damage is done, isn't it?

01:29:14.680 --> 01:29:15.920
I got to go.

01:29:15.920 --> 01:29:19.470
James.

01:29:19.470 --> 01:29:24.069
David, get out of my way.

01:29:24.069 --> 01:29:28.590
James, I know that sorry doesn't cut it.

01:29:28.590 --> 01:29:32.229
But please, just one minute.

01:29:32.229 --> 01:29:36.140
Just to hear me out.

01:29:36.140 --> 01:29:40.319
For all the bad things that I've done,

01:29:40.319 --> 01:29:46.130
and I know now how much you cared about me,

01:29:46.130 --> 01:29:53.899
how much you loved me, and I didn't care.

01:29:53.899 --> 01:29:55.579
I wouldn't listen.

01:29:55.579 --> 01:30:04.260
You were right about so many things.

01:30:04.260 --> 01:30:11.289
But now I'm asking you, as the one that I used to look up to,

01:30:11.289 --> 01:30:16.210
as the one that taught me how to swing a hammer, James,

01:30:16.210 --> 01:30:23.640
I'm asking you, as the one that taught me to beat me, James,

01:30:23.640 --> 01:30:30.470
I'm asking you, is your little brother?

01:30:30.470 --> 01:30:35.859
Please forgive me.

01:30:35.859 --> 01:30:44.720
Because if you can't, I can't live with myself.

01:30:44.720 --> 01:31:26.100
Sorry.

01:31:26.100 --> 01:31:27.300
Careful, bro.

01:31:27.300 --> 01:31:28.500
Don't mess up your clothes.

01:31:28.500 --> 01:31:36.720
I'm good.

01:31:36.720 --> 01:31:38.119
I should be good now.

01:31:38.119 --> 01:31:39.239
Won't you fish get ready?

01:31:39.239 --> 01:31:43.439
How do I mind if I've plenty of time?

01:31:43.439 --> 01:31:44.760
Breakfast is ready.

01:31:44.760 --> 01:31:45.520
Yes.

01:31:45.520 --> 01:31:47.359
We should have everything roughed in for you

01:31:47.359 --> 01:31:49.720
by tomorrow morning latest.

01:31:49.720 --> 01:31:52.119
Exactly.

01:31:52.119 --> 01:31:52.960
All right then.

01:31:52.960 --> 01:31:54.159
We'll see you.

01:31:54.159 --> 01:31:54.880
Thank you so much.

01:31:54.880 --> 01:31:56.720
Bye-bye.

01:31:56.720 --> 01:31:59.359
Honey, after we leave, could you call the township

01:31:59.359 --> 01:32:02.600
and have them schedule the inspector for Friday?

01:32:02.600 --> 01:32:03.680
Sure.

01:32:03.680 --> 01:32:04.920
What about Ed Brewster?

01:32:04.920 --> 01:32:06.760
When do you need him next week?

01:32:06.760 --> 01:32:09.199
I'm going to need him a few days, so let's wait

01:32:09.199 --> 01:32:10.680
and see what the boys have scheduled first.

01:32:10.680 --> 01:32:11.680
It's great to meet you.

01:32:11.680 --> 01:32:13.479
Mom, those are the things.

01:32:13.479 --> 01:32:16.199
My mom is really good.

01:32:16.199 --> 01:32:17.520
Oh, did you want to call Johnny and Mel?

01:32:17.520 --> 01:32:18.800
See if they can play some ball tonight?

01:32:19.800 --> 01:32:21.720
Yeah, actually, I'm supposed to work out

01:32:21.720 --> 01:32:23.840
in service of Johnny this morning, so I'll ask him.

01:32:23.840 --> 01:32:25.840
And then I'll call Mel at lunch.

01:32:25.840 --> 01:32:28.640
And then I'll check to make sure the courts are open.

01:32:28.640 --> 01:32:30.960
OK, so David, what's your schedule

01:32:30.960 --> 01:32:32.000
looking like for next week?

01:32:32.000 --> 01:32:34.560
Well, I was hoping to go out in service on Wednesday and Friday

01:32:34.560 --> 01:32:36.880
and then plan in to work the other days.

01:32:36.880 --> 01:32:38.279
Perfect, how about you, James?

01:32:38.279 --> 01:32:41.000
Well, if I go out on Monday, I'll have my time for the month,

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:43.159
so I can start work Tuesday.

01:32:43.159 --> 01:32:44.640
Good.

01:32:44.640 --> 01:32:46.479
Well, that's good, because I'll need both of you

01:32:46.479 --> 01:32:48.840
to help me finish the punch list at the Mitchell House,

01:32:48.840 --> 01:32:51.279
and then I can call for the final inspection.

01:32:51.279 --> 01:32:53.800
You're telling me you got your time in for the month already?

01:32:53.800 --> 01:32:55.399
How'd you manage that?

01:32:55.399 --> 01:32:56.960
All in the scheduling, bro.

01:32:56.960 --> 01:33:00.199
Start early in the day, early in the week, early in the month.

01:33:00.199 --> 01:33:03.239
And early in the year, that's what everyone's been saying.

01:33:03.239 --> 01:33:05.199
I hope I can make it work.

01:33:05.199 --> 01:33:06.520
I know you will.

01:33:06.520 --> 01:33:09.560
When you start pioneering, we'll make a good team.

01:33:09.560 --> 01:33:11.039
Yeah, we will.

01:33:11.039 --> 01:33:14.170
I'm looking forward to it.

01:33:14.170 --> 01:33:17.960
James, you want to read our theme text this morning?

01:33:17.960 --> 01:33:21.039
Staying from 1 Corinthians 13, 13.

01:33:21.039 --> 01:33:25.720
Now, however, the remained faith, hope, love, these three.

01:33:25.720 --> 01:33:29.119
But the greatest of these is love.

01:33:29.119 --> 01:33:32.840
So it looks like we're talking about love this morning.

01:33:32.840 --> 01:33:34.199
David, you want to read our comments?

01:33:34.199 --> 01:33:36.359
Sure.

01:33:36.359 --> 01:33:38.680
Now, among Jehovah's people today,

01:33:38.680 --> 01:33:44.000
we see the wisdom of pursuing the surpassing way of love.

01:33:44.000 --> 01:33:48.600
Truly, it excels in any and all situations.

01:33:48.600 --> 01:33:52.399
Note how the Apostle Paul emphasized that truth.

01:33:52.399 --> 01:33:57.800
He concluded, now, however, their remained faith, hope, love,

01:33:57.800 --> 01:33:59.319
these three.

01:33:59.319 --> 01:34:01.960
But the greatest of these is love.
